    "description": "Clinical escalation rules for the CDST Rule Engine. These rules determine when a patient must be urgently referred to a First Referral Unit (FRU) or higher. Includes a conditional escalation policy for pregnancy where doctor review is required if a pregnancy-sensitive diagnosis or teratogen is involved.",
